notesStmt.note: Front damp and mouldy, with tidemarks.
Repaired and infilled before rebinding, older repairs obscure text.
Usage stains, liquid spills, ink smears.
Some ink burn-through in later parts of the manuscript.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 25; written lines: 25; Uniform layout. From folio 9r onwards, abbreviation in the upper right corner of each page: בעה (be-ezrat ha-Shem) Catchwords on every page in latter part. Folios marked on versos, in the right-hand upper corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental square and semi-cursive script of the 18th century.

binding.p: BM in-house. Spine: 'A Collection of Liturgical Poems. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 4855.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: E.B. Frankel: purchased by the British Museum on 19 January 1895: inscribed, flyleaf [iii]v.
